title: one-pot irish stew
steps: ['Place the lamb in a large pot, cover with water and add a pinch of salt.', 'Bring to the boil; skim off any white fat that comes to the surface, then simmer on low heat for another 30 minutes.', 'Add the onion and half of the potatoes and cook for 30 minutes until the potatoes are soft; break them up and stir - this will thicken the stew.', 'Add the remaining potatoes and carrots.', 'Simmer for another 20-30 minutes until potatoes are cooked.', 'Season well with salt and pepper to taste.', 'Stir in fresh parsley or chopped leeks.', 'Serve piping hot.']
why_question: Why must Step 5 happen after Step 1?
model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: one-pot irish stew

Procedure:
1. Place the lamb in a large pot, cover with water and add a pinch of salt.
2. Bring to the boil; skim off any white fat that comes to the surface, then simmer on low heat for another 30 minutes.
3. Add the onion and half of the potatoes and cook for 30 minutes until the potatoes are soft; break them up and stir - this will thicken the stew.
4. Add the remaining potatoes and carrots.
5. Simmer for another 20-30 minutes until potatoes are cooked.
6. Season well with salt and pepper to taste.
7. Stir in fresh parsley or chopped leeks.
8. Serve piping hot.

2. Bring to the boil; skim off any white fat that comes to the surface, then simmer on low heat for another 30 minutes.
3. Add the onion and half of the potatoes and cook for 30 minutes until the potatoes are soft; break them up and stir - this will thicken the stew.
4. Add the remaining potatoes and carrots.

title: peppers-with-tuna-and-mushrooms
steps: ['Heat 2 tbsp olive oil in a frying pan and add 1 chopped onion.', 'Cook for 5 minutes or until softened.', 'Add 250g halved or quartered chestnut mushrooms.', 'Season and cook, stirring occasionally, until the mushrooms give up their juices.', 'Add 1 tbsp wholegrain mustard, the grated zest of 1 lemon, 1 crushed garlic clove and 4 tbsp dry sherry.', 'Cook, stirring until the mushrooms are evenly coated with a little sauce.', 'Meanwhile, drain and slice a 280g jar of roasted red peppers.', 'Mix the peppers into the mushrooms and heat gently for 1 minute.', 'Finally, stir in a 185g can tuna, drained, and 25g chopped fresh parsley.', 'Serve immediately, with crisp salad leaves and plenty of hot crusty bread or boiled rice.']
why_question: Why must Step 2 happen after Step 1?
model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: peppers-with-tuna-and-mushrooms

Procedure:
1. Heat 2 tbsp olive oil in a frying pan and add 1 chopped onion.
2. Cook for 5 minutes or until softened.
3. Add 250g halved or quartered chestnut mushrooms.
4. Season and cook, stirring occasionally, until the mushrooms give up their juices.
5. Add 1 tbsp wholegrain mustard, the grated zest of 1 lemon, 1 crushed garlic clove and 4 tbsp dry sherry.
6. Cook, stirring until the mushrooms are evenly coated with a little sauce.
7. Meanwhile, drain and slice a 280g jar of roasted red peppers.
8. Mix the peppers into the mushrooms and heat gently for 1 minute.
9. Finally, stir in a 185g can tuna, drained, and 25g chopped fresh parsley.
10. Serve immediately, with crisp salad leaves and plenty of hot crusty bread or boiled rice.

Goal: peppers-with-tuna-and-mushrooms

1. Heat 2 tbsp olive oil in a frying pan and add 1 chopped onion.

title: simple-basic-cupcakes
steps: ['Preheat oven to 180 C / Gas 4.', 'Beat butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.', 'Add the eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.', 'If the batter is too thick, stir in some milk.', 'Gradually add the flour, mixing well each time until evenly mixed.', 'Spoon tablespoons of batter into a greased muffin tin.', 'Bake in preheated oven for 15-20 minutes.', 'The cake is done when a skewer inserted to the cake comes out clean.', 'Let rest for fives minutes, then allow to cool fully on a wire rack.', 'Decorate, if desired.']

model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: simple-basic-cupcakes

Procedure:
1. Preheat oven to 180 C / Gas 4.
2. Beat butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
3. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
4. If the batter is too thick, stir in some milk.
5. Gradually add the flour, mixing well each time until evenly mixed.
6. Spoon tablespoons of batter into a greased muffin tin.
7. Bake in preheated oven for 15-20 minutes.
8. The cake is done when a skewer inserted to the cake comes out clean.
9. Let rest for fives minutes, then allow to cool fully on a wire rack.
10. Decorate, if desired.

1. Preheat oven to 180 C / Gas 4.
2. Beat butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
3. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
4. If the batter is too thick, stir in some milk.
5. Gradually add the flour, mixing well each time until evenly mixed.
6. Spoon tablespoons of batter into a greased muffin tin.
7. Bake in preheated oven for 15-20 minutes.
8. The cake is done when a skewer inserted to the cake comes out clean.
9. Let rest for fives minutes, then allow to cool fully on a wire rack.
10. Decorate, if desired.


Must Step 5 happen after Step 1? Select between yes or no

steps: ['Heat the butter and vegetable oil in a large frying pan over medium heat.', 'Stir in the chicken, onion and garlic.', 'Cook and stir until the onion has softened and turned translucent, about 10 minutes.', 'Stir in the curry powder, curry paste, tandoori masala, garam masala and tomato puree until no lumps of tomato puree remain.', 'Pour into a slow cooker, and stir in the cardamom pods, coconut milk and yoghurt.', 'Season to taste with salt.', 'Cook on High 4 to 6 hours, or on Low 6 to 8 hours until the chicken is tender and the sauce has reduced to your desired consistency.', 'Remove and discard the cardamom pods before serving.']

model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: slow cooker butter chicken

Procedure:
1. Heat the butter and vegetable oil in a large frying pan over medium heat.
2. Stir in the chicken, onion and garlic.
3. Cook and stir until the onion has softened and turned translucent, about 10 minutes.
4. Stir in the curry powder, curry paste, tandoori masala, garam masala and tomato puree until no lumps of tomato puree remain.
5. Pour into a slow cooker, and stir in the cardamom pods, coconut milk and yoghurt.
6. Season to taste with salt.
7. Cook on High 4 to 6 hours, or on Low 6 to 8 hours until the chicken is tender and the sauce has reduced to your desired consistency.
8. Remove and discard the cardamom pods before serving.

Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: smoked-salmon-and-grapefruit-salad

Procedure:
1. Top and tail the grapefruits.
2. Slice the skin off the grapefruit over a bowl.
3. This is to catch any juices.
4. Using a small knife, segment the grapefruits over the juice bowl.
5. Arrange the lamb's lettuce onto each serving plate or a large salad bowl.
6. Top with grapefruit segments and smoked salmon.
7. Mix together 1 pinch of cracked peppercorns and 1 tablespoon grapefruit juice from the bowl.
8. Pour over the salad and serve.

6. Top with grapefruit segments and smoked salmon.
7. Mix together 1 pinch of cracked peppercorns and 1 tablespoon grapefruit juice from the bowl.
8. Pour over the salad and serve.

model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: spanish-rabbit-stew

Procedure:
1. After slicing all of your ingredients, throw them all into your slow cooker (everything in at once, couldn’t be easier right?
2. ).
3. I like to mix mine up, so I can take a big scoop and get a lovely mix of goodness.
4. Pour in half pint of white wine and half pint of water.
5. You might want to add a little more of each to cover your ingredients but the key rule is to keep the mixture 50/50.
6. Make sure your tarragon and bay leaf aren’t floating on the top or it won't let off any real flavour.
7. Turn your slow cooker on to low power, let it simmer for about 5 hours.
8. If your aren’t hungry once that wonderful smell fills the room, I’ll refund the cost of the ingredients!
9. Flavour with salt and pepper to taste.
10. Cook the pasta according to the packet instructions, and serve with pasta.
11. Most importantly, enjoy!

1. After slicing all of your ingredients, throw them all into your slow cooker (everything in at once, couldn’t be easier right?
2. ).
3. I like to mix mine up, so I can take a big scoop and get a lovely mix of goodness.
4. Pour in half pint of white wine and half pint of water.
5. You might want to add a little more of each to cover your ingredients but the key rule is to keep the mixture 50/50.
6. Make sure your tarragon and bay leaf aren’t floating on the top or it won't let off any real flavour.
7. Turn your slow cooker on to low power, let it simmer for about 5 hours.
8. If your aren’t hungry once that wonderful smell fills the room, I’ll refund the cost of the ingredients!
9. Flavour with salt and pepper to taste.
10. Cook the pasta according to the packet instructions, and serve with pasta.
11. Most importantly, enjoy!

title: spiced butternut squash soup
steps: ['Preheat the oven to 190 C / Gas mark 6.', 'Pour a small layer of water in a baking dish, or a swiss roll tin.', 'Place the squash halves cut side down on the dish.', 'Bake for about 40 minutes, or until a fork can easily pierce the flesh.', 'Cool slightly, then remove the peel.', 'Set aside.', 'Melt the butter in a large pot over medium heat.', 'Add the onion, leek and garlic, and saute for a few minutes, until tender.', 'Pour the chicken stock into the pot.', 'Add the potatoes, and bring to the boil.', 'Cook for about 20 minutes, or until soft.', 'Add the squash, and mash with the potatoes until chunks are small.', 'Use an immersion hand blender to puree the soup, or transfer to a blender or food processor in batches, and puree until smooth.', 'Return to the pot.', 'Season the soup with cayenne pepper, allspice, nutmeg, ginger, salt and pepper, then stir in the sherry, cream and milk.', 'Heat through, but do not boil.', 'Ladle into bowls, and top with a dollop of soured cream if desired.']
why_question: Why must Step 2 happen after Step 1?
model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: spiced butternut squash soup

Procedure:
1. Preheat the oven to 190 C / Gas mark 6.
2. Pour a small layer of water in a baking dish, or a swiss roll tin.
3. Place the squash halves cut side down on the dish.
4. Bake for about 40 minutes, or until a fork can easily pierce the flesh.
5. Cool slightly, then remove the peel.
6. Set aside.
7. Melt the butter in a large pot over medium heat.
8. Add the onion, leek and garlic, and saute for a few minutes, until tender.
9. Pour the chicken stock into the pot.
10. Add the potatoes, and bring to the boil.
11. Cook for about 20 minutes, or until soft.
12. Add the squash, and mash with the potatoes until chunks are small.
13. Use an immersion hand blender to puree the soup, or transfer to a blender or food processor in batches, and puree until smooth.
14. Return to the pot.
15. Season the soup with cayenne pepper, allspice, nutmeg, ginger, salt and pepper, then stir in the sherry, cream and milk.
16. Heat through, but do not boil.
17. Ladle into bowls, and top with a dollop of soured cream if desired.

1. Preheat the oven to 190 C / Gas mark 6.
2. Pour a small layer of water in a baking dish, or a swiss roll tin.
3. Place the squash halves cut side down on the dish.
4. Bake for about 40 minutes, or until a fork can easily pierce the flesh.
5. Cool slightly, then remove the peel.
6. Set aside.
7. Melt the butter in a large pot over medium heat.
8. Add the onion, leek and garlic, and saute for a few minutes, until tender.
9. Pour the chicken stock into the pot.
10. Add the potatoes, and bring to the boil.
11. Cook for about 20 minutes, or until soft.
12. Add the squash, and mash with the potatoes until chunks are small.
13. Use an immersion hand blender to puree the soup, or transfer to a blender or food processor in batches, and puree until smooth.
14. Return to the pot.
15. Season the soup with cayenne pepper, allspice, nutmeg, ginger, salt and pepper, then stir in the sherry, cream and milk.
16. Heat through, but do not boil.
17. Ladle into bowls, and top with a dollop of soured cream if desired.


Must Step 5 happen after Step 1? Select between yes or no

Goal: spiced butternut squash soup

Procedure:
1. Preheat the oven to 190 C / Gas mark 6.
2. Pour a small layer of water in a baking dish, or a swiss roll tin.

Goal: spiced butternut squash soup

2. Pour a small layer of water in a baking dish, or a swiss roll tin.

Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: spiced butternut squash soup

Procedure:
1. Preheat the oven to 190 C / Gas mark 6.
2. Pour a small layer of water in a baking dish, or a swiss roll tin.
3. Place the squash halves cut side down on the dish.
4. Bake for about 40 minutes, or until a fork can easily pierce the flesh.
5. Cool slightly, then remove the peel.

14. Return to the pot.

16. Heat through, but do not boil.
17. Ladle into bowls, and top with a dollop of soured cream if desired.

title: spiced-guava-cake
steps: ['Preheat oven to 180 C / Gas 4.', 'Grease and flour one 23x13cm loaf tin.', 'Sieve together flour, cornflour, nutmeg, bicarbonate of soda, cinnamon and cloves.', 'In another bowl, mix together guava pulp and juice.', 'In another bowl, cream together butter and sugar.', 'Add eggs, one at a time.', 'Add flour mixture and guava mixture alternately to creamed mixture.', 'Pour batter into prepared tin.', 'Bake at 180 C / Gas 4 for 30-35 minutes.']
why_question: Why must Step 2 happen after Step 1?
model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: spiced-guava-cake

Procedure:
1. Preheat oven to 180 C / Gas 4.
2. Grease and flour one 23x13cm loaf tin.
3. Sieve together flour, cornflour, nutmeg, bicarbonate of soda, cinnamon and cloves.
4. In another bowl, mix together guava pulp and juice.
5. In another bowl, cream together butter and sugar.
6. Add eggs, one at a time.
7. Add flour mixture and guava mixture alternately to creamed mixture.
8. Pour batter into prepared tin.
9. Bake at 180 C / Gas 4 for 30-35 minutes.

steps: ['Preheat the oven to 180尊C (350尊F, gas mark 4).', 'Line a 900 g (2 lb) loaf tin with baking parchment.', 'Steam the pumpkin flesh, or cook it in just a little boiling water, for 10 minutes or until tender.', 'Drain thoroughly, then mash with a potato masher until smooth.', 'Add the honey and sultanas, and beat well.', 'Sift the wholemeal and white flours and the allspice into a bowl, tipping in any bran left in the sieve.', 'Rub in the butter with your fingertips until the mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs.', 'Add the pumpkin mixture and beat well with a wooden spoon until evenly mixed.', 'Tip the mixture into the prepared tin and smooth the surface.', 'Sprinkle with the pumpkin seeds.', 'Bake for 50 minutes or until the loaf is well risen, golden brown and firm to the touch.', 'Allow the loaf to cool in the tin for 10 minutes, then turn it out onto a wire rack.', 'Gently brush with the 2 tsp honey while still warm.', 'This teabread is best served slightly warm, or within a day of making.']
why_question: Why must Step 2 happen after Step 1?
model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: spiced-pumpkin-teabread

Procedure:
1. Preheat the oven to 180尊C (350尊F, gas mark 4).
2. Line a 900 g (2 lb) loaf tin with baking parchment.
3. Steam the pumpkin flesh, or cook it in just a little boiling water, for 10 minutes or until tender.
4. Drain thoroughly, then mash with a potato masher until smooth.
5. Add the honey and sultanas, and beat well.
6. Sift the wholemeal and white flours and the allspice into a bowl, tipping in any bran left in the sieve.
7. Rub in the butter with your fingertips until the mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs.
8. Add the pumpkin mixture and beat well with a wooden spoon until evenly mixed.
9. Tip the mixture into the prepared tin and smooth the surface.
10. Sprinkle with the pumpkin seeds.
11. Bake for 50 minutes or until the loaf is well risen, golden brown and firm to the touch.
12. Allow the loaf to cool in the tin for 10 minutes, then turn it out onto a wire rack.
13. Gently brush with the 2 tsp honey while still warm.
14. This teabread is best served slightly warm, or within a day of making.

Goal: spiced-pumpkin-teabread

Procedure:
1. Preheat the oven to 180尊C (350尊F, gas mark 4).
2. Line a 900 g (2 lb) loaf tin with baking parchment.
3. Steam the pumpkin flesh, or cook it in just a little boiling water, for 10 minutes or until tender.
4. Drain thoroughly, then mash with a potato masher until smooth.
5. Add the honey and sultanas, and beat well.

14. This teabread is best served slightly warm, or within a day of making.

model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: spiced-pumpkin-teabread

Procedure:
1. Preheat the oven to 180尊C (350尊F, gas mark 4).
2. Line a 900 g (2 lb) loaf tin with baking parchment.
3. Steam the pumpkin flesh, or cook it in just a little boiling water, for 10 minutes or until tender.
4. Drain thoroughly, then mash with a potato masher until smooth.
5. Add the honey and sultanas, and beat well.
6. Sift the wholemeal and white flours and the allspice into a bowl, tipping in any bran left in the sieve.
7. Rub in the butter with your fingertips until the mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs.
8. Add the pumpkin mixture and beat well with a wooden spoon until evenly mixed.
9. Tip the mixture into the prepared tin and smooth the surface.
10. Sprinkle with the pumpkin seeds.
11. Bake for 50 minutes or until the loaf is well risen, golden brown and firm to the touch.
12. Allow the loaf to cool in the tin for 10 minutes, then turn it out onto a wire rack.
13. Gently brush with the 2 tsp honey while still warm.
14. This teabread is best served slightly warm, or within a day of making.

steps: ['Preheat the oven to 180尊C (350尊F, gas mark 4).', 'Line a 900 g (2 lb) loaf tin with baking parchment.', 'Steam the pumpkin flesh, or cook it in just a little boiling water, for 10 minutes or until tender.', 'Drain thoroughly, then mash with a potato masher until smooth.', 'Add the honey and sultanas, and beat well.', 'Sift the wholemeal and white flours and the allspice into a bowl, tipping in any bran left in the sieve.', 'Rub in the butter with your fingertips until the mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs.', 'Add the pumpkin mixture and beat well with a wooden spoon until evenly mixed.', 'Tip the mixture into the prepared tin and smooth the surface.', 'Sprinkle with the pumpkin seeds.', 'Bake for 50 minutes or until the loaf is well risen, golden brown and firm to the touch.', 'Allow the loaf to cool in the tin for 10 minutes, then turn it out onto a wire rack.', 'Gently brush with the 2 tsp honey while still warm.', 'This teabread is best served slightly warm, or within a day of making.']

model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: spiced-pumpkin-teabread

Procedure:
1. Preheat the oven to 180尊C (350尊F, gas mark 4).
2. Line a 900 g (2 lb) loaf tin with baking parchment.
3. Steam the pumpkin flesh, or cook it in just a little boiling water, for 10 minutes or until tender.
4. Drain thoroughly, then mash with a potato masher until smooth.
5. Add the honey and sultanas, and beat well.
6. Sift the wholemeal and white flours and the allspice into a bowl, tipping in any bran left in the sieve.
7. Rub in the butter with your fingertips until the mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs.
8. Add the pumpkin mixture and beat well with a wooden spoon until evenly mixed.
9. Tip the mixture into the prepared tin and smooth the surface.
10. Sprinkle with the pumpkin seeds.
11. Bake for 50 minutes or until the loaf is well risen, golden brown and firm to the touch.
12. Allow the loaf to cool in the tin for 10 minutes, then turn it out onto a wire rack.
13. Gently brush with the 2 tsp honey while still warm.
14. This teabread is best served slightly warm, or within a day of making.

title: spicy-tomato-anchovy-pasta
steps: ['Heat 6 tablespoons olive oil in a large frying pan over medium heat, then stir in garlic, broccoli and mushrooms;', 'cook until lightly browned.', 'Add anchovies and water, cover and simmer for 4 to 5 minutes.', 'Stir in spring onions, tomatoes and parsley and cover again, simmering until vegetables are soft, about 3 to 4 minutes.', 'While the vegetables are cooking, bring a large pot of water and one teaspoon of olive oil to the boil.', 'Add linguine and cook until al dente, about 7 to 8 minutes;', 'drain.', 'Toss with anchovy mixture and chilli flakes.', 'If desired, season with black pepper.', 'Serve immediately.']
why_question: Why must Step 2 happen after Step 1?
model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: spicy-tomato-anchovy-pasta

Procedure:
1. Heat 6 tablespoons olive oil in a large frying pan over medium heat, then stir in garlic, broccoli and mushrooms;
2. cook until lightly browned.
3. Add anchovies and water, cover and simmer for 4 to 5 minutes.
4. Stir in spring onions, tomatoes and parsley and cover again, simmering until vegetables are soft, about 3 to 4 minutes.
5. While the vegetables are cooking, bring a large pot of water and one teaspoon of olive oil to the boil.
6. Add linguine and cook until al dente, about 7 to 8 minutes;
7. drain.
8. Toss with anchovy mixture and chilli flakes.
9. If desired, season with black pepper.
10. Serve immediately.

1. Heat 6 tablespoons olive oil in a large frying pan over medium heat, then stir in garlic, broccoli and mushrooms;

model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: spicy-tomato-anchovy-pasta

Procedure:
1. Heat 6 tablespoons olive oil in a large frying pan over medium heat, then stir in garlic, broccoli and mushrooms;
2. cook until lightly browned.
3. Add anchovies and water, cover and simmer for 4 to 5 minutes.
4. Stir in spring onions, tomatoes and parsley and cover again, simmering until vegetables are soft, about 3 to 4 minutes.
5. While the vegetables are cooking, bring a large pot of water and one teaspoon of olive oil to the boil.
6. Add linguine and cook until al dente, about 7 to 8 minutes;
7. drain.
8. Toss with anchovy mixture and chilli flakes.
9. If desired, season with black pepper.
10. Serve immediately.

title: strawberry-tiramisu-trifle
steps: ['Set 3 strawberries for the garnish aside, and cut the rest into slices.', 'In a large bowl, beat the cream cheese with a hand whisk until creamy, gradually adding 2 tablespoons of the coffee.', 'Then stir in the custard and finally fold in the whipped cream.', 'Brush the sponge fingers with the remaining coffee.', 'Line a glass bowl with one layer of the soaked sponge fingers.', 'Spread half of the strawberries over the sponge fingers.', 'Sprinkle half of the grated chocolate over that and then half of the custard mixture.', 'Repeat the layers in order again.', 'Cut the remaining 3 strawberries in half and lay them on top of the trifle.', 'Cover and leave in the fridge for at least 4 hours, best overnight.']
why_question: Why must Step 2 happen after Step 1?
model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: strawberry-tiramisu-trifle

Procedure:
1. Set 3 strawberries for the garnish aside, and cut the rest into slices.
2. In a large bowl, beat the cream cheese with a hand whisk until creamy, gradually adding 2 tablespoons of the coffee.
3. Then stir in the custard and finally fold in the whipped cream.
4. Brush the sponge fingers with the remaining coffee.
5. Line a glass bowl with one layer of the soaked sponge fingers.
6. Spread half of the strawberries over the sponge fingers.
7. Sprinkle half of the grated chocolate over that and then half of the custard mixture.
8. Repeat the layers in order again.
9. Cut the remaining 3 strawberries in half and lay them on top of the trifle.
10. Cover and leave in the fridge for at least 4 hours, best overnight.


Must Step 2 happen after Step 1? Select between yes or no

model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: strawberry-tiramisu-trifle

Procedure:
1. Set 3 strawberries for the garnish aside, and cut the rest into slices.
2. In a large bowl, beat the cream cheese with a hand whisk until creamy, gradually adding 2 tablespoons of the coffee.
3. Then stir in the custard and finally fold in the whipped cream.
4. Brush the sponge fingers with the remaining coffee.
5. Line a glass bowl with one layer of the soaked sponge fingers.
6. Spread half of the strawberries over the sponge fingers.
7. Sprinkle half of the grated chocolate over that and then half of the custard mixture.
8. Repeat the layers in order again.
9. Cut the remaining 3 strawberries in half and lay them on top of the trifle.
10. Cover and leave in the fridge for at least 4 hours, best overnight.

title: tangy-gammon-in-cider
steps: ['Preheat the oven to 200 degrees /gas mark 6.', 'Start by piercing each tomato once and covering with boiling water to loosen the skins.', 'Drain the onions and chop each one in half.', 'Once the tomatoes have been in the water for 5 minutes, drain, then remove the skins and coarsely chop into largish pieces.', 'Put the onions, tomatoes and apples into a casserole dish.', 'Take a gammon steak, lay flat, and spoon some of the mixture into the middle, then wrap the sides of the steak over the top and secure with a small skewer or piece of raw spaghetti.', 'Place in the dish and repeat with the other gammon steaks.', 'Pour cider over the steaks, cover the top with a lid or tin foil.', 'Cook for 1 hour.']
why_question: Why must Step 2 happen after Step 1?
model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: tangy-gammon-in-cider

Procedure:
1. Preheat the oven to 200 degrees /gas mark 6.
2. Start by piercing each tomato once and covering with boiling water to loosen the skins.
3. Drain the onions and chop each one in half.
4. Once the tomatoes have been in the water for 5 minutes, drain, then remove the skins and coarsely chop into largish pieces.
5. Put the onions, tomatoes and apples into a casserole dish.
6. Take a gammon steak, lay flat, and spoon some of the mixture into the middle, then wrap the sides of the steak over the top and secure with a small skewer or piece of raw spaghetti.
7. Place in the dish and repeat with the other gammon steaks.
8. Pour cider over the steaks, cover the top with a lid or tin foil.
9. Cook for 1 hour.


Must Step 2 happen after Step 1? Select between yes or no

steps: ['Preheat the oven to 200 degrees /gas mark 6.', 'Start by piercing each tomato once and covering with boiling water to loosen the skins.', 'Drain the onions and chop each one in half.', 'Once the tomatoes have been in the water for 5 minutes, drain, then remove the skins and coarsely chop into largish pieces.', 'Put the onions, tomatoes and apples into a casserole dish.', 'Take a gammon steak, lay flat, and spoon some of the mixture into the middle, then wrap the sides of the steak over the top and secure with a small skewer or piece of raw spaghetti.', 'Place in the dish and repeat with the other gammon steaks.', 'Pour cider over the steaks, cover the top with a lid or tin foil.', 'Cook for 1 hour.']

model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: tangy-gammon-in-cider

Procedure:
1. Preheat the oven to 200 degrees /gas mark 6.
2. Start by piercing each tomato once and covering with boiling water to loosen the skins.
3. Drain the onions and chop each one in half.
4. Once the tomatoes have been in the water for 5 minutes, drain, then remove the skins and coarsely chop into largish pieces.
5. Put the onions, tomatoes and apples into a casserole dish.
6. Take a gammon steak, lay flat, and spoon some of the mixture into the middle, then wrap the sides of the steak over the top and secure with a small skewer or piece of raw spaghetti.
7. Place in the dish and repeat with the other gammon steaks.
8. Pour cider over the steaks, cover the top with a lid or tin foil.
9. Cook for 1 hour.

model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: vegetable-terrine

Procedure:
1. Add the gelatin in a bowl of cold water until soft.
2. Heat the stock and cook the vegetables one after the other in the stock (15 minutes for the carrots and beans, 10 minutes for courgettes and celeriac, 5 minutes for the peas).
3. Run the vegetables under cold water to stop them cooking.
4. Wash the sorrel, add the olive oil to a frying pan and cook for 3 minutes, chop then set aside.
5. In a saucepan, bring cream and yogurt to the boil.
6. Add the chopped sorrel and gelatin.
7. Mix well and remove from heat.
8. Set aside and cool for a few minutes.
9. Pour approximately 1cm of the cream mixture into a mould and refrigerate.
10. It is better to use a silicone mould, it will be easier to remove for serving.
11. Arrange the vegetables, alternating according to shape, starting with the matchstick vegetables on the bottom and peas in the middle.
12. Pour the remaining cream mixture on top.
13. Refrigerate the terrine for several hours until firm.
14. If you did'nt use a silicone mould, immerse the mould in boiling water then turn it over - it should release.
15. Serve chilled.


Must Step 2 happen after Step 1? Select between yes or no

model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: vegetable-terrine

Procedure:
1. Add the gelatin in a bowl of cold water until soft.
2. Heat the stock and cook the vegetables one after the other in the stock (15 minutes for the carrots and beans, 10 minutes for courgettes and celeriac, 5 minutes for the peas).
3. Run the vegetables under cold water to stop them cooking.
4. Wash the sorrel, add the olive oil to a frying pan and cook for 3 minutes, chop then set aside.
5. In a saucepan, bring cream and yogurt to the boil.
6. Add the chopped sorrel and gelatin.
7. Mix well and remove from heat.
8. Set aside and cool for a few minutes.
9. Pour approximately 1cm of the cream mixture into a mould and refrigerate.
10. It is better to use a silicone mould, it will be easier to remove for serving.
11. Arrange the vegetables, alternating according to shape, starting with the matchstick vegetables on the bottom and peas in the middle.
12. Pour the remaining cream mixture on top.
13. Refrigerate the terrine for several hours until firm.
14. If you did'nt use a silicone mould, immerse the mould in boiling water then turn it over - it should release.
15. Serve chilled.

Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: vegetable-terrine

Procedure:
1. Add the gelatin in a bowl of cold water until soft.
2. Heat the stock and cook the vegetables one after the other in the stock (15 minutes for the carrots and beans, 10 minutes for courgettes and celeriac, 5 minutes for the peas).
3. Run the vegetables under cold water to stop them cooking.
4. Wash the sorrel, add the olive oil to a frying pan and cook for 3 minutes, chop then set aside.
5. In a saucepan, bring cream and yogurt to the boil.
6. Add the chopped sorrel and gelatin.
7. Mix well and remove from heat.
8. Set aside and cool for a few minutes.
9. Pour approximately 1cm of the cream mixture into a mould and refrigerate.
10. It is better to use a silicone mould, it will be easier to remove for serving.
11. Arrange the vegetables, alternating according to shape, starting with the matchstick vegetables on the bottom and peas in the middle.
12. Pour the remaining cream mixture on top.
13. Refrigerate the terrine for several hours until firm.
14. If you did'nt use a silicone mould, immerse the mould in boiling water then turn it over - it should release.
15. Serve chilled.

model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: very-vanilla-ry-cheesecake

Procedure:
1. Preheat oven to 150 C / Gas 2 and lightly butter a 26cm springform tin.
2. Place the biscuits into a plastic bag and crush with a rolling pin.
3. Pour the crumbs into a bowl and mix with the scraped seeds of 1 vanilla bean.
4. Drizzle the crumbs with melted butter and stir to combine.
5. Press the crumb mixture firmly into the bottom and up the sides of the springform tin and set aside.
6. Place the softened cream cheese and sugar into the work bowl of an electric mixer and beat for about 3 minutes on Medium speed, until the mixture is smooth.
7. Beat in the eggs one at a time, incorporating each egg before adding the next one.
8. Add the scraped seeds of 2 vanilla beans, vanilla extract, soured cream and double cream and beat on Medium-High speed for about 1 minute, until the mixture is blended and smooth.
9. Pour the mixture into the biscuit base, leaving about 5cm of space from the top of the tin for the cake to expand as it bakes.
10. Place a baking dish onto the bottom rack of the preheated oven and fill it halfway with boiling water.
11. Place the cheesecake onto the middle rack, above the tin of boiling water and bake until a small knife inserted into the middle of the cheesecake comes out clean, about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
12. Turn the oven off and let the cheesecake cool down inside the oven for 1 hour.
13. Cover the cheesecake with cling film, then foil and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight before serving.

model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: very-vanilla-ry-cheesecake

Procedure:
1. Preheat oven to 150 C / Gas 2 and lightly butter a 26cm springform tin.
2. Place the biscuits into a plastic bag and crush with a rolling pin.
3. Pour the crumbs into a bowl and mix with the scraped seeds of 1 vanilla bean.
4. Drizzle the crumbs with melted butter and stir to combine.
5. Press the crumb mixture firmly into the bottom and up the sides of the springform tin and set aside.
6. Place the softened cream cheese and sugar into the work bowl of an electric mixer and beat for about 3 minutes on Medium speed, until the mixture is smooth.
7. Beat in the eggs one at a time, incorporating each egg before adding the next one.
8. Add the scraped seeds of 2 vanilla beans, vanilla extract, soured cream and double cream and beat on Medium-High speed for about 1 minute, until the mixture is blended and smooth.
9. Pour the mixture into the biscuit base, leaving about 5cm of space from the top of the tin for the cake to expand as it bakes.
10. Place a baking dish onto the bottom rack of the preheated oven and fill it halfway with boiling water.
11. Place the cheesecake onto the middle rack, above the tin of boiling water and bake until a small knife inserted into the middle of the cheesecake comes out clean, about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
12. Turn the oven off and let the cheesecake cool down inside the oven for 1 hour.
13. Cover the cheesecake with cling film, then foil and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight before serving.

model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: very-vanilla-ry-cheesecake

Procedure:
1. Preheat oven to 150 C / Gas 2 and lightly butter a 26cm springform tin.
2. Place the biscuits into a plastic bag and crush with a rolling pin.
3. Pour the crumbs into a bowl and mix with the scraped seeds of 1 vanilla bean.
4. Drizzle the crumbs with melted butter and stir to combine.
5. Press the crumb mixture firmly into the bottom and up the sides of the springform tin and set aside.
6. Place the softened cream cheese and sugar into the work bowl of an electric mixer and beat for about 3 minutes on Medium speed, until the mixture is smooth.
7. Beat in the eggs one at a time, incorporating each egg before adding the next one.
8. Add the scraped seeds of 2 vanilla beans, vanilla extract, soured cream and double cream and beat on Medium-High speed for about 1 minute, until the mixture is blended and smooth.
9. Pour the mixture into the biscuit base, leaving about 5cm of space from the top of the tin for the cake to expand as it bakes.
10. Place a baking dish onto the bottom rack of the preheated oven and fill it halfway with boiling water.
11. Place the cheesecake onto the middle rack, above the tin of boiling water and bake until a small knife inserted into the middle of the cheesecake comes out clean, about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
12. Turn the oven off and let the cheesecake cool down inside the oven for 1 hour.
13. Cover the cheesecake with cling film, then foil and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight before serving.

model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: very-vanilla-ry-cheesecake

Procedure:
1. Preheat oven to 150 C / Gas 2 and lightly butter a 26cm springform tin.
2. Place the biscuits into a plastic bag and crush with a rolling pin.
3. Pour the crumbs into a bowl and mix with the scraped seeds of 1 vanilla bean.
4. Drizzle the crumbs with melted butter and stir to combine.
5. Press the crumb mixture firmly into the bottom and up the sides of the springform tin and set aside.
6. Place the softened cream cheese and sugar into the work bowl of an electric mixer and beat for about 3 minutes on Medium speed, until the mixture is smooth.
7. Beat in the eggs one at a time, incorporating each egg before adding the next one.
8. Add the scraped seeds of 2 vanilla beans, vanilla extract, soured cream and double cream and beat on Medium-High speed for about 1 minute, until the mixture is blended and smooth.
9. Pour the mixture into the biscuit base, leaving about 5cm of space from the top of the tin for the cake to expand as it bakes.
10. Place a baking dish onto the bottom rack of the preheated oven and fill it halfway with boiling water.
11. Place the cheesecake onto the middle rack, above the tin of boiling water and bake until a small knife inserted into the middle of the cheesecake comes out clean, about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
12. Turn the oven off and let the cheesecake cool down inside the oven for 1 hour.
13. Cover the cheesecake with cling film, then foil and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight before serving.

model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: very-vanilla-ry-cheesecake

Procedure:
1. Preheat oven to 150 C / Gas 2 and lightly butter a 26cm springform tin.
2. Place the biscuits into a plastic bag and crush with a rolling pin.
3. Pour the crumbs into a bowl and mix with the scraped seeds of 1 vanilla bean.
4. Drizzle the crumbs with melted butter and stir to combine.
5. Press the crumb mixture firmly into the bottom and up the sides of the springform tin and set aside.
6. Place the softened cream cheese and sugar into the work bowl of an electric mixer and beat for about 3 minutes on Medium speed, until the mixture is smooth.
7. Beat in the eggs one at a time, incorporating each egg before adding the next one.
8. Add the scraped seeds of 2 vanilla beans, vanilla extract, soured cream and double cream and beat on Medium-High speed for about 1 minute, until the mixture is blended and smooth.
9. Pour the mixture into the biscuit base, leaving about 5cm of space from the top of the tin for the cake to expand as it bakes.
10. Place a baking dish onto the bottom rack of the preheated oven and fill it halfway with boiling water.
11. Place the cheesecake onto the middle rack, above the tin of boiling water and bake until a small knife inserted into the middle of the cheesecake comes out clean, about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
12. Turn the oven off and let the cheesecake cool down inside the oven for 1 hour.
13. Cover the cheesecake with cling film, then foil and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight before serving.

model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: very-vanilla-ry-cheesecake

Procedure:
1. Preheat oven to 150 C / Gas 2 and lightly butter a 26cm springform tin.
2. Place the biscuits into a plastic bag and crush with a rolling pin.
3. Pour the crumbs into a bowl and mix with the scraped seeds of 1 vanilla bean.
4. Drizzle the crumbs with melted butter and stir to combine.
5. Press the crumb mixture firmly into the bottom and up the sides of the springform tin and set aside.
6. Place the softened cream cheese and sugar into the work bowl of an electric mixer and beat for about 3 minutes on Medium speed, until the mixture is smooth.
7. Beat in the eggs one at a time, incorporating each egg before adding the next one.
8. Add the scraped seeds of 2 vanilla beans, vanilla extract, soured cream and double cream and beat on Medium-High speed for about 1 minute, until the mixture is blended and smooth.
9. Pour the mixture into the biscuit base, leaving about 5cm of space from the top of the tin for the cake to expand as it bakes.
10. Place a baking dish onto the bottom rack of the preheated oven and fill it halfway with boiling water.
11. Place the cheesecake onto the middle rack, above the tin of boiling water and bake until a small knife inserted into the middle of the cheesecake comes out clean, about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
12. Turn the oven off and let the cheesecake cool down inside the oven for 1 hour.
13. Cover the cheesecake with cling film, then foil and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight before serving.

model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: very-vanilla-ry-cheesecake

Procedure:
1. Preheat oven to 150 C / Gas 2 and lightly butter a 26cm springform tin.
2. Place the biscuits into a plastic bag and crush with a rolling pin.
3. Pour the crumbs into a bowl and mix with the scraped seeds of 1 vanilla bean.
4. Drizzle the crumbs with melted butter and stir to combine.
5. Press the crumb mixture firmly into the bottom and up the sides of the springform tin and set aside.
6. Place the softened cream cheese and sugar into the work bowl of an electric mixer and beat for about 3 minutes on Medium speed, until the mixture is smooth.
7. Beat in the eggs one at a time, incorporating each egg before adding the next one.
8. Add the scraped seeds of 2 vanilla beans, vanilla extract, soured cream and double cream and beat on Medium-High speed for about 1 minute, until the mixture is blended and smooth.
9. Pour the mixture into the biscuit base, leaving about 5cm of space from the top of the tin for the cake to expand as it bakes.
10. Place a baking dish onto the bottom rack of the preheated oven and fill it halfway with boiling water.
11. Place the cheesecake onto the middle rack, above the tin of boiling water and bake until a small knife inserted into the middle of the cheesecake comes out clean, about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
12. Turn the oven off and let the cheesecake cool down inside the oven for 1 hour.
13. Cover the cheesecake with cling film, then foil and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight before serving.

Goal: warm-puy-lentil-and-tomato-salad

Procedure:
1. Bring a large pan of water to the boil;
2. add lentils and cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
3. Put tomatoes in a small bowl and season with salt.

5. Drain lentils and tomatoes and mix together.

title: white bread
steps: ['In a large bowl, dissolve the sugar in warm water, and then stir in yeast.', 'Allow to proof until yeast resembles a creamy foam.', 'Mix salt and oil into the yeast mixture.', 'Mix in flour about 125g at a time.', 'Knead dough on a lightly floured surface until smooth.', 'Place in a well oiled bowl, and turn dough to coat.', 'Cover with a damp cloth.', 'Allow to rise until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.', 'Punch dough down.', 'Knead for a few minutes, and divide in half.', 'Shape into loaves, and place into two well oiled 23x13cm (9x5 in) loaf tins.', 'Allow to rise for 30 minutes, or until dough has risen 2.5cm (1 in) above tins.', 'Bake in a preheated 180 C / Gas 4 oven for 30 minutes.']
why_question: Why must Step 2 happen after Step 1?
model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: white bread

Procedure:
1. In a large bowl, dissolve the sugar in warm water, and then stir in yeast.
2. Allow to proof until yeast resembles a creamy foam.
3. Mix salt and oil into the yeast mixture.
4. Mix in flour about 125g at a time.
5. Knead dough on a lightly floured surface until smooth.
6. Place in a well oiled bowl, and turn dough to coat.
7. Cover with a damp cloth.
8. Allow to rise until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
9. Punch dough down.
10. Knead for a few minutes, and divide in half.
11. Shape into loaves, and place into two well oiled 23x13cm (9x5 in) loaf tins.
12. Allow to rise for 30 minutes, or until dough has risen 2.5cm (1 in) above tins.
13. Bake in a preheated 180 C / Gas 4 oven for 30 minutes.

model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: white bread

Procedure:
1. In a large bowl, dissolve the sugar in warm water, and then stir in yeast.
2. Allow to proof until yeast resembles a creamy foam.
3. Mix salt and oil into the yeast mixture.
4. Mix in flour about 125g at a time.
5. Knead dough on a lightly floured surface until smooth.
6. Place in a well oiled bowl, and turn dough to coat.
7. Cover with a damp cloth.
8. Allow to rise until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
9. Punch dough down.
10. Knead for a few minutes, and divide in half.
11. Shape into loaves, and place into two well oiled 23x13cm (9x5 in) loaf tins.
12. Allow to rise for 30 minutes, or until dough has risen 2.5cm (1 in) above tins.
13. Bake in a preheated 180 C / Gas 4 oven for 30 minutes.

model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: white bread

Procedure:
1. In a large bowl, dissolve the sugar in warm water, and then stir in yeast.
2. Allow to proof until yeast resembles a creamy foam.
3. Mix salt and oil into the yeast mixture.
4. Mix in flour about 125g at a time.
5. Knead dough on a lightly floured surface until smooth.
6. Place in a well oiled bowl, and turn dough to coat.
7. Cover with a damp cloth.
8. Allow to rise until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
9. Punch dough down.
10. Knead for a few minutes, and divide in half.
11. Shape into loaves, and place into two well oiled 23x13cm (9x5 in) loaf tins.
12. Allow to rise for 30 minutes, or until dough has risen 2.5cm (1 in) above tins.
13. Bake in a preheated 180 C / Gas 4 oven for 30 minutes.

model_input:
Given a goal, a procedure to achieve that goal and a question about the steps in the procedure, you are required to answer the question in one sentence.

Goal: white bread

Procedure:
1. In a large bowl, dissolve the sugar in warm water, and then stir in yeast.
2. Allow to proof until yeast resembles a creamy foam.
3. Mix salt and oil into the yeast mixture.
4. Mix in flour about 125g at a time.
5. Knead dough on a lightly floured surface until smooth.
6. Place in a well oiled bowl, and turn dough to coat.
7. Cover with a damp cloth.
8. Allow to rise until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
9. Punch dough down.
10. Knead for a few minutes, and divide in half.
11. Shape into loaves, and place into two well oiled 23x13cm (9x5 in) loaf tins.
12. Allow to rise for 30 minutes, or until dough has risen 2.5cm (1 in) above tins.
13. Bake in a preheated 180 C / Gas 4 oven for 30 minutes.
